<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Distribution of Navarretia divaricata (black squares) occurrences across its native range in the western United States." , "Figure 1. Navarretia divaricata. A Pressed specimen showing plant habit, scale bar = 1 cm (Johnson 14 - 143) B Flowering head in the field, scale bar = 2 mm (Johnson 15 - 045) C-E Equivalent magnification, scale bar = 2 mm C Pressed flowering head showing typical coloration of dried flowers (Johnson 16 - 024) D Dried fruit, showing dehiscence from base upward typical in all of the species detailed herein (Johnson 16 - 024) E Fresh flowering head dissected with corolla removed to show style and two-lobed stigma (with third lobe nearly entirely fused to one of the two apparent lobes; Johnson 16 - 024) F, G Fresh flowers showing typical coloration (Johnson 15 - 045), equivalent magnification, scale bar = 2 mm. All photographs by L. A. Johnson and vouchers deposited at BRY." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/172425" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/172424" .

